TestCase.name: NTHLRB-605
TestCase.Description:
Testcase: NTHLRB-605
Title: Subscriber without O-CSI - RSI with all CSI 'induce' - Run UL - Add/replace/delete OCSI.
Purpose:
Prerequisites: 1) RDSP flag is set to SOLD and ACTIVE 2) A simple GSM subscriber is exists in C-NTDB with RSI attached 3) RSI has 'induce' treatment for OCSI outside HPLMN.
Request: 1) Perform HPLMN LUP. 2) Attach O-CSI to the subscriber. 3) Perform FPLMN LUP. 4) Replace O-CSI to the subscriber. 5) Perform LUP from HPLMN Country. 6) Remove O-CSI from the subscriber.
Result: 1) LUP is successful. No OCSI data downloaded in HPLMN. 2) ISD is triggered with the OCSI data. 3) LUP successful with the induced OCSI data. 4) No ISD triggered. 5) LUP successful with the induced OCSI data. 6) No ISD triggered.

TestCase.name: NTHLRB-606
TestCase.Description:
Testcase: NTHLRB-605
Title: Subscriber without O-CSI - RSI with all CSI 'induce' - Run UL - Add/replace/delete OCSI.
Purpose:
Prerequisites: 1) RDSP flag is set to SOLD and ACTIVE 2) A simple GSM subscriber is exists in C-NTDB with RSI attached 3) RSI has 'induce' treatment for OCSI outside HPLMN.
Request: 1) Perform HPLMN LUP. 2) Attach O-CSI to the subscriber. 3) Perform FPLMN LUP. 4) Replace O-CSI to the subscriber. 5) Perform LUP from HPLMN Country. 6) Remove O-CSI from the subscriber.
Result: 1) LUP is successful. No OCSI data downloaded in HPLMN. 2) ISD is triggered with the OCSI data. 3) LUP successful with the induced OCSI data. 4) No ISD triggered. 5) LUP successful with the induced OCSI data. 6) No ISD triggered.

TestCase.name: NTHLRB-607
TestCase.Description:
Testcase: NTHLRB-605
Title: Subscriber without O-CSI - RSI with all CSI 'induce' - Run UL - Add/replace/delete OCSI.
Purpose:
Prerequisites: 1) RDSP flag is set to SOLD and ACTIVE 2) A simple GSM subscriber is exists in C-NTDB with RSI attached 3) RSI has 'induce' treatment for OCSI outside HPLMN.
Request: 1) Perform HPLMN LUP. 2) Attach O-CSI to the subscriber. 3) Perform FPLMN LUP. 4) Replace O-CSI to the subscriber. 5) Perform LUP from HPLMN Country. 6) Remove O-CSI from the subscriber.
Result: 1) LUP is successful. No OCSI data downloaded in HPLMN. 2) ISD is triggered with the OCSI data. 3) LUP successful with the induced OCSI data. 4) No ISD triggered. 5) LUP successful with the induced OCSI data. 6) No ISD triggered.
